  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train 120 Health &amp; Human Rights promoters in Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HFAW will work with the 30 new graduates in health and human rights to train 120 new promoters in 4 locations, in Nyamira. The new tots will use transformative strategies based on popular education which has been highly effective in Chile (via EPES Foundation) changing the lives of poor women and will focuses on reproductive health and human rights as critical step to break the epidemic discrimination against women. HFAW has produced highly motivated women (&amp;men) ready to scale up the methods.</narrative>
  </description>
